Subject: [PATCH] gl/egl: define EGL_PLATFORM_SURFACELESS_MESA fallback

gst1-plugins-base 1.24.13 references EGL_PLATFORM_SURFACELESS_MESA in
gst_gl_display_egl_get_from_native() but, unlike every other EGL_PLATFORM_*
value used in the same file, it does not provide a fallback #define for it.

Recent Mesa (>= 25.2, shipped by Buildroot 2025.11.x / nerves_system_br 1.33.9)
installs stripped-down EGL headers (eglext.h / eglmesaext.h) that no longer
declare EGL_PLATFORM_SURFACELESS_MESA, so the cross build fails with:

  gstgldisplay_egl.c: error: 'EGL_PLATFORM_SURFACELESS_MESA' undeclared

Add the missing fallback (0x31DD, the canonical Mesa value), matching the
surrounding code that already does this for X11/WAYLAND/GBM_MESA/etc.

Upstream-Status: backport candidate (gst-plugins-base)
Signed-off-by: kiosk_system_recomputer_r11xx

--- a/gst-libs/gst/gl/egl/gstgldisplay_egl.c
+++ b/gst-libs/gst/gl/egl/gstgldisplay_egl.c
@@ -62,6 +62,9 @@
 #ifndef EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_ANGLE
 #define EGL_PLATFORM_ANGLE_ANGLE 0x3202
 #endif
+#ifndef EGL_PLATFORM_SURFACELESS_MESA
+#define EGL_PLATFORM_SURFACELESS_MESA 0x31DD
+#endif

 typedef EGLDisplay (*_gst_eglGetPlatformDisplay_type) (EGLenum platform,
     void *native_display, const EGLint * attrib_list);
